Subject: apps.json: add "Gamescope Steam Session" default entry

User request: a Steam streaming target that runs through Gamescope so the
session behaves like SteamOS Gaming Mode — forced fullscreen, FSR
upscaling, tight refresh-rate handling, FIFO-paced presentation.

NOTE: an earlier revision passed `--immediate-flips`. Diagnosis traced
the 49-58fps "stream cap" symptom to that flag: in nested-wayland mode
`--immediate-flips` bypasses kwin's frame-callback throttling, so
gamescope committed buffers to its kwin parent faster than the EDID's
60Hz, kwin propagated each commit as fresh damage on the EVDI surface
(~90 events/s), and Apollo's encoder dropped the over-rate via the
`time_diff < -frame_variation_threshold` path (-> popped 90/s, encoded
53/s, skipped 38/s on real streams). Replacing `--immediate-flips` with
`-o $(APOLLO_CLIENT_FPS)` caps gamescope's render-loop FPS to the
client's negotiated rate, lets it FIFO-pace presentation, and matches
kwin's 60Hz pageflip cadence end-to-end.

Gamescope (gamescope 3.16+, already a CachyOS package) is a micro-
compositor designed for game presentation. Nesting it inside kwin on
the EVDI virtual display gives us:

  - `-f` fullscreen exclusive (no kwin window decorations / panels)
  - `-r <fps>` lock-step refresh matching the client target
  - `--upscale-filter fsr --upscale-sharpness 4` FSR 1.0 upscaling
    (games can render at lower internal res for perf; gamescope
    upscales to the EVDI buffer's resolution)
  - `-o $(APOLLO_CLIENT_FPS)` cap nested compositor output rate to
    the client's negotiated FPS (paired with `-r` advertising the
    same value — `-r` is advisory, `-o` enforces)
  - `-e` Steam integration (gamepad input routing, app lifecycle)
  - When gamescope exits, the wrapping `steam -bigpicture` exits too,
    cleanly ending the Apollo session

The entry uses Apollo's existing env-var substitution to inherit the
client's negotiated dimensions:
   gamescope -W $(APOLLO_CLIENT_WIDTH) -H $(APOLLO_CLIENT_HEIGHT)
             -r $(APOLLO_CLIENT_FPS) ...
APOLLO_CLIENT_FPS is already in integer Hz (process.cpp converts from
the mHz wire value), so no /1000 needed.

`virtual-display: true` triggers EVDI display creation (patches 0001-
0007); `wait-all: true` keeps Apollo holding the session until
gamescope exits.

Adds `gamescope` to PKGBUILD optdepends so the package metadata
documents the requirement without making it a hard dep (other Apollo
use cases work without it).

--- a/src_assets/linux/assets/apps.json
+++ b/src_assets/linux/assets/apps.json
@@ -31,6 +31,16 @@
         "setsid steam steam://open/bigpicture"
       ],
       "image-path": "steam.png"
+    },
+    {
+      "name": "Gamescope Steam Session",
+      "image-path": "steam.png",
+      "virtual-display": true,
+      "auto-detach": false,
+      "wait-all": true,
+      "exit-timeout": 5,
+      "scale-factor": 100,
+      "cmd": "gamescope --backend=wayland -W $(APOLLO_CLIENT_WIDTH) -H $(APOLLO_CLIENT_HEIGHT) -r $(APOLLO_CLIENT_FPS) -o $(APOLLO_CLIENT_FPS) -f -e --upscale-filter fsr --upscale-sharpness 4 -- steam -bigpicture"
     }
   ]
 }
